Closer to Cuba than to Miami, Key West is Florida’s southernmost island paradise. Connected to the mainland by the Overseas Highway, this famed little spot was home to the likes of Ernest Hemingway, Tennessee Williams, Robert Frost and Jimmy Buffett. With palm lined streets, gingerbread mansions, and pastel-hued conch houses, the island’s culture sees a mix of Bahamian and Cuban influence.

Have you visited Key West yet? 

Over the next week, I’ll be taking y’all along on my Florida Keys adventure. 🗺️🐚 Let me know if there’s anything you’d like to see in The Keys or learn about while I’m here! 

📍: Key West, @thefloridakeys 
📸: @___ulfho___

Key Largo is the first island of the Florida Keys. It’s name is derived from Cayo Largo, which is Spanish for "long key.” Surrounded by the warm waters of the Florida Bay, the Florida Straits, and the Atlantic Ocean, Key Largo is a water lover’s paradise.

Day 1 of Valentine’s Day inspired eats: Truffle honey, peach & brie filo tart 👩🏽‍🍳💋 Recipe below. 

Grab some 🍯 for your 🍯 at savouryimports.com. 

Follow the whole series on TikTok or on @savouryimports ! 

To make: line baking tin with parchment paper and begin to layer ready-to-use filo pastry, brushing each sheet with oil [optional: for extra crispy tart, put a light layer of breadcrumbs between each layer]. 

Top with brie cheese, peach slices, thyme or rosemary, basil, La Madia Truffle Honey, truffle salt, and pine nuts. 
Bake in oven at 350degrees F until edges are golden brown, cheese is melted, and peaches are tender. Brush edges with additional oil or egg wash. 

**chef’s note: I’ve also done this recipe with puff pastry—and both options are so delicious. Choose your pastry based on your [and your boo’s] personal preference and you can’t go wrong. 

Enjoy!!!

Quebec Road Trip with Turo

Getting there: Turo rental
From filtering down my options through my preferences and essentials,  the renting experience through the Turo app was absolutely seamless. Given the miles I’d be driving from Toronto to Montreal to Mont Tremblant, I made sure to select a vehicle that not only offered unlimited milage, but one that would be comfortable both on the city streets and in the backcountry roads. As a peer-to-peer car rental platform, Turo allows users to browse available cars in their desired location, book their preferred vehicle, and then arrange for pickup or delivery directly with the car owner. With various protection plans available and 24/7 customer support, the whole experience allows renters some peace of mind. 

Montreal stay: Hotel Monville 
With large windows looking out onto a beautiful view of Montreal’s city streets, this laid-back, design-minded hotel is tech-savvy in the best ways possible—think robots, remote controlled blinds, a top-of-the-line gym, high-definition TVs, and more. 

Mont Tremblant stay: La Khabine 
Surrounded by trees, this cute and cozy stay is an absolute hidden gem. From the floor to ceiling windows to the cedar barrel sauna, La Khabine is a relaxing oasis in an idyllic location— one that is remote enough to feel in the middle of nature, but close enough to still enjoy the luxuries of small town life. 

Food & Drink: 
Yoko Luna: Serving up one of the best dinner experiences I‘ve had in awhile, Yoko Luna was the perfect blend of delicious cuisine, stunning decor and entertaining performances—with a touch of Japanese influence in all three, our night spent at Yoko Luna was not one to be forgotten any time soon.

Schwartz‘s Deli: This iconic deli in Montreal is a classic for a reason—and is even considered a Montreal landmark. Getting your hands on one of their world famous Montreal smoked meat sandwiches will usually entail a line, so make sure to leave yourself plenty of time for your meal!

The HighAcre • Leaving this beautiful boutique spa hotel feeling rejuvenated & inspired. From the bones of an 1867 farm house, The HighAcre has been transformed into a haven for rest & relaxation. Each room has a private ensuite spa inclusive of an infrared sauna, steam room and bathtub—perfect for hot & cold plunges. 

As soon as I drove onto the property, I felt as though I had been transported to the European countryside. As I discovered the different cozy details that made this stay bucket list worthy, I fell more and more in love. From the ready-to-bake croissants in the fridge, to the gorgeous fireplace that warmed the room, I can’t wait to share more about this spa hotel as part of my Great Escapes series with @streetsoftoronto 🤍

📍: @thehighacre

POV: you indulge in a winter staycation at Bisha Hotel ❄️

From the in room soaker tubs (y’all know they’re my fave) to their new speakeasy, Parlour 712, it’s always a treat staying at Bisha. 

Parlour 712 is a converted suite, tucked away on the 7th floor, designed by Lenny Kravitz’ design team. This hidden spot is accessible to hotel guests only and is open Fridays and Saturdays. It features a daily-changing password for entry, as well as offers complimentary drinks courtesy of DALMORE Whiskey! As an extra bonus, there is a beautiful heated winter dome on the terrace ❄️😍

Cheers to the perfect winter escape—right in the heart of the city!
